762
00:43:54,423 --> 00:43:55,799
So I didn't even try.

763
00:44:01,221 --> 00:44:02,222
That lunatic.

764
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:05,851
That's why he turned his victims around
to see the faces in the light.

765
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:14,860
{\an8}<i>There's a case from January 2004
in Bongu-dong, Bucheon.</i>

766
00:44:14,943 --> 00:44:17,029
{\an8}<i>A ten-year-old boy was kidnapped,
raped, and murdered.</i>

767
00:44:17,112 --> 00:44:18,781
<i>I'll print the materials for you.</i>

768
00:44:19,365 --> 00:44:20,574
BONGU-DONG

769
00:44:23,118 --> 00:44:24,495
BONGU-DONG KIDNAPPING AND MURDER

770
00:44:26,288 --> 00:44:29,583
BONGU-DONG ELEMENTARY STUDENT
MURDER CASE LEFT UNSOLVED

771
00:44:30,167 --> 00:44:33,712
Does anyone happen to know about
a case from two years ago in Bongu-dong?

772
00:44:33,796 --> 00:44:36,715
Where a ten-year-old boy was
kidnapped, raped, and murdered?

773
00:44:37,675 --> 00:44:39,760
I saw it when I was picking out cases
for us to work on.

774
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:40,886
Bongu-dong?

775
00:44:41,387 --> 00:44:44,765
Isn't it the cold case from two years ago
that was extensively reported on?

776
00:44:47,726 --> 00:44:49,395
Give me the fax number here, please.

777
00:44:55,401 --> 00:44:57,528
RECEIVING SCAN

778
00:44:58,195 --> 00:44:59,863
I guess the more I watch them,

779
00:45:01,448 --> 00:45:04,451
the more I want to try
something more violent.

780
00:45:05,077 --> 00:45:07,037
So you kept changing your murder weapon.

781
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:09,373
At first, I liked
the feeling of strangling.

782
00:45:09,456 --> 00:45:12,835
That feeling when they flap about
when they run out of breath.

783
00:45:15,045 --> 00:45:19,174
It was more euphoric than I had imagined
when I tried it myself.

784
00:45:19,258 --> 00:45:21,552
You keep using the expression, "euphoric."

785
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:25,514
I feel like it expresses the best feeling.

786
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:31,145
Anyway…

787
00:45:32,980 --> 00:45:36,358
After I came home that day,
I slept like a baby.

788
00:45:36,942 --> 00:45:38,402
-Because you felt euphoric?
-Yes.

789
00:45:38,944 --> 00:45:42,156
Oh, right. Then I tried using a knife.

790
00:45:42,239 --> 00:45:45,367
Watching the blood pumping out
made me go crazy.

791
00:45:45,951 --> 00:45:48,036
I was so happy. It was so thrilling.

792
00:45:49,705 --> 00:45:51,582
I sometimes went back
to the neighborhood I killed in

793
00:45:51,665 --> 00:45:53,292
and reminisced about it too.

794
00:45:54,751 --> 00:45:56,420
-Reminisce?
-Yes.

795
00:45:58,213 --> 00:45:59,798
You liked the knife so much.

796
00:46:01,508 --> 00:46:03,260
Why did you switch to a pipe wrench?

797
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:06,805
I wanted to feel
a different sensation from a knife.

798
00:46:08,390 --> 00:46:10,184
Was that after Pureumae Park?

799
00:46:10,267 --> 00:46:11,351
Maybe.

800
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:16,148
I get a little confused
because there are so many.

801
00:46:16,857 --> 00:46:20,068
When I used a small knife,
they wouldn't die very easily.

802
00:46:20,152 --> 00:46:22,112
So I switched to a kitchen knife.

803
00:46:22,196 --> 00:46:24,072
But it didn't really do the job.

804
00:46:24,781 --> 00:46:26,742
It got me annoyed and angry
for some reason.

805
00:46:26,825 --> 00:46:29,495
It made me uncomfortable and annoyed
if they didn't die.

806
00:46:29,578 --> 00:46:30,787
Why would you get annoyed?

807
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:34,291
That should not happen in a perfect crime.

808
00:46:35,834 --> 00:46:38,712
I was trying to commit the perfect crime.

809
00:46:38,795 --> 00:46:40,506
So I didn't rape the girls I killed.

810
00:46:41,173 --> 00:46:43,175
-In case you might leave evidence?
-Yes.

811
00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:47,346
No matter how hot it was,
I didn't take my gloves off.

812
00:46:48,931 --> 00:46:51,558
Even though the gloves
dulled the sensation a little.

813
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:55,062
The steel pipe had its perks too,
so it was all right.

814
00:46:57,147 --> 00:46:59,358
That I can stand
if I want to kill more for long.

815
00:47:01,026 --> 00:47:02,986
What is the sensation
you're talking about?

816
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:06,949
The head is the weakest part of a human.

817
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:11,119
The moment you strike it down like this…

818
00:47:12,788 --> 00:47:15,624
You'll never understand what I mean
unless you try it yourself.

819
00:47:15,707 --> 00:47:18,043
The blood splatters everywhere.

820
00:47:18,126 --> 00:47:19,836
That's when the victims flap about.

821
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:22,381
That's the moment that makes me go crazy.

822
00:47:22,464 --> 00:47:24,716
I'm thrilled to death.

823
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:27,427
Watching it makes me so happy and elated.

824
00:47:28,929 --> 00:47:30,472
You've never tried it,
so you have no idea.

825
00:47:33,225 --> 00:47:35,561
Gosh, I can't listen to him anymore.

826
00:47:35,644 --> 00:47:38,105
How does he stand listening to him?

827
00:47:39,064 --> 00:47:41,233
This isn't a job for the weak-minded.

828
00:47:41,316 --> 00:47:44,069
I have a weak mind.

829
00:47:44,152 --> 00:47:45,904
I'm going to step out for a moment.

830
00:47:51,034 --> 00:47:52,160
I need to pee.

831
00:47:53,662 --> 00:47:55,789
-You want to use the bathroom?
-Yes.

832
00:48:01,753 --> 00:48:03,463
Hold on. The detectives will be here.

833
00:48:04,631 --> 00:48:06,967
-You'll wait for me, right?
-Yes.

834
00:48:08,051 --> 00:48:09,428
I will be right back.

835
00:48:10,637 --> 00:48:11,888
Sure. Take your time.

836
00:48:14,975 --> 00:48:15,851
Hey.

837
00:48:17,978 --> 00:48:20,689
-You gave me a signal earlier, right?
-Yes.

838
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:24,109
You think this was
Nam Ki-Tae's doing too, right?

839
00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:25,944
I do.

840
00:48:26,028 --> 00:48:29,156
The way the ten-year-old boy's fingers
were tied up by a shoelace.

841
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:31,867
The same thing happened
to Nam Ki-Tae in his childhood.

842
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:34,578
We should interrogate him then.

843
00:48:34,661 --> 00:48:37,372
How far does his area of crime
stretch out?

844
00:48:38,999 --> 00:48:40,334
I'm going to go back in.

845
00:48:41,543 --> 00:48:42,461
Ha-young.

846
00:48:46,256 --> 00:48:48,550
You can leave it
to the detectives in charge here.

847
00:48:49,176 --> 00:48:50,927
You don't have to do everything.

848
00:48:52,429 --> 00:48:54,890
Nam Ki-Tae and I already formed a rapport.

849
00:48:55,766 --> 00:48:58,560
-I'll get his confession the fastest.
-Yes, that's true.

850
00:49:01,188 --> 00:49:03,607
But all those horrible things
that he's pouring out…

851
00:49:04,191 --> 00:49:06,360
There's no need for you
to bear it all yourself.

852
00:49:06,443 --> 00:49:07,778
I wouldn't have even started…

853
00:49:08,654 --> 00:49:10,238
if I was going to avoid it.

854
00:49:10,947 --> 00:49:11,990
You're right.

855
00:49:12,991 --> 00:49:14,618
I worried for nothing.

856
00:49:14,701 --> 00:49:15,911
-I'll be back.
-Okay.

857
00:49:23,001 --> 00:49:24,836
INTERROGATION ROOM

858
00:49:31,551 --> 00:49:32,886
You get scared easily, right?

859
00:49:33,887 --> 00:49:34,805
Me?

860
00:49:34,888 --> 00:49:38,308
You chose to commit crimes
only around Seoul and Gyeonggi,

861
00:49:38,392 --> 00:49:39,810
in neighborhoods close to you.

862
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:41,978
What if I get caught
going to a foreign place?

863
00:49:42,062 --> 00:49:43,146
For your perfect crime?

864
00:49:44,981 --> 00:49:47,901
-That's why you ran with all your might?
-How did you know I ran every day?

865
00:49:47,984 --> 00:49:50,570
-You ran every day?
-You didn't know then.

866
00:49:51,321 --> 00:49:53,490
I thought you knew that too,
so I was shocked.

867
00:49:53,573 --> 00:49:55,909
I saw you wrote down
running methods in your notes.

868
00:49:55,992 --> 00:49:59,121
I ran around the school's field ten times.
I didn't miss a single day.

869
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:02,666
So running is the one thing
I'm confident about.

870
00:50:03,208 --> 00:50:04,251
Wait, no.

871
00:50:05,293 --> 00:50:06,920
I'm good at killing people too.

872
00:50:07,003 --> 00:50:09,172
Once I started going
to different neighborhoods,

873
00:50:09,756 --> 00:50:11,466
it made me want to visit Busan too.

874
00:50:12,050 --> 00:50:13,677
I couldn't go because I got caught.

875
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:17,055
Weren't you scared when the news
started to focus its attention on you?

876
00:50:17,139 --> 00:50:18,348
Why would I be scared?

877
00:50:18,432 --> 00:50:19,683
You might get caught.

878
00:50:21,101 --> 00:50:22,227
Gu Young-chun.

879
00:50:24,146 --> 00:50:25,605
He said he was scared, right?

880
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:27,107
Why are you bringing him up?

881
00:50:27,190 --> 00:50:28,942
That punk is a loser.

882
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:33,321
I liked trying to avoid the police.
I found it very thrilling.

883
00:50:33,905 --> 00:50:35,490
-Thrilling?
-Yes.

884
00:50:39,828 --> 00:50:42,247
Do you still feel no remorse
towards those people?

885
00:50:42,330 --> 00:50:43,498
Why would I feel remorse?

886
00:50:44,708 --> 00:50:47,252
I'm not sorry at all.
I don't even feel guilty.

887
00:50:48,837 --> 00:50:51,506
All I wanted to do was kill more people.

888
00:50:53,717 --> 00:50:57,179
When I saw what I did on the TV,
I felt like I became a hero.

889
00:50:58,013 --> 00:51:00,557
I felt proud
thinking that I killed that person.

890
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:01,975
Then I felt like the TV…

891
00:51:06,396 --> 00:51:07,439
What was that?

892
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:13,320
You were proud
and felt like a hero, right?

893
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:17,532
You took a ten-year-old kid
to the woods in Bongu-dong,

894
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:19,117
tied up his fingers with shoelaces,

895
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:23,580
then committed the atrocity
you experienced to that little kid.

896
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:26,708
Isn't that so?

897
00:51:26,792 --> 00:51:28,710
Why are you suddenly getting angry?

898
00:51:30,045 --> 00:51:31,797
Will anything change if I confess?

899
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:33,256
If you don't confess,

900
00:51:33,840 --> 00:51:36,593
people like Gu Young-chun
will bluff and say they did it.

901
00:51:36,676 --> 00:51:37,761
Damn it.

902
00:51:38,553 --> 00:51:39,930
I did it.

903
00:51:46,436 --> 00:51:48,814
FINGER WAS TIED WITH SHOELACES
JUNG WAS PLAYING SOCCER WITH FRIENDS

904
00:51:48,897 --> 00:51:50,607
What was he doing at that time?

905
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:53,360
-He was playing with a ball.
-Be specific.

906
00:51:53,443 --> 00:51:54,486
Soccer.

907
00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:57,531
Happy now?

908
00:51:57,614 --> 00:51:59,658
I'll share the details
with the detectives.

909
00:52:03,829 --> 00:52:05,664
Can I go back to what I was saying?

910
00:52:07,499 --> 00:52:09,417
Do you enjoy talking about
stuff like this?

911
00:52:09,501 --> 00:52:10,585
It's fun.

912
00:52:11,545 --> 00:52:14,047
No one has ever listened to me before.

913
00:52:14,130 --> 00:52:16,424
Why do you think
people don't want to talk to you?

914
00:52:16,508 --> 00:52:18,552
They're all normal,
but I seem like a psycho.

915
00:52:18,635 --> 00:52:19,970
A psycho?

916
00:52:20,053 --> 00:52:23,014
You know, confused and anxious.

917
00:52:24,516 --> 00:52:27,227
This confusion often drives me insane too.

918
00:52:27,310 --> 00:52:28,937
I'm sure I seem weird to others.

919
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:31,481
And you were freed from such emotions
when you killed?

920
00:52:31,565 --> 00:52:32,899
I told you already.

921
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:34,943
That's why I can't stop.

922
00:52:37,863 --> 00:52:39,489
When I stab,

923
00:52:39,573 --> 00:52:42,409
I try to avoid the parts
where the blood would spatter.

924
00:52:42,492 --> 00:52:44,286
I stab in the ribs or stomach.

925
00:52:44,369 --> 00:52:48,707
Then I can feel all the different
sensations from the knife going in.

926
00:52:50,208 --> 00:52:52,794
You should see
the expressions on their faces.

927
00:52:52,878 --> 00:52:54,546
You never know unless you see it.

928
00:52:56,381 --> 00:52:58,008
I want to do it again.

929
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:00,635
I think you're less than a beast.

930
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:02,846
What do you think?

931
00:53:06,766 --> 00:53:07,976
You're not a hero.

932
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:13,148
You seem like an angry lunatic
who just throws his knife around.

933
00:53:13,231 --> 00:53:14,274
You're right.

934
00:53:16,234 --> 00:53:17,444
I never denied that.

935
00:53:21,448 --> 00:53:22,699
Let me continue.

936
00:53:22,782 --> 00:53:24,075
You're going to continue?

937
00:53:24,159 --> 00:53:27,704
I couldn't share this with anyone,
so I was really frustrated.

938
00:53:28,288 --> 00:53:29,748
It's now or never, right?

939
00:53:29,831 --> 00:53:31,166
So stay and listen.

940
00:53:32,792 --> 00:53:34,753
Among many ways of killing,

941
00:53:34,836 --> 00:53:37,297
my favorite is
hitting someone on the head.

942
00:53:37,380 --> 00:53:40,008
As I mentioned before, it's the flapping.

943
00:53:40,091 --> 00:53:42,886
It feels awesome to watch them flap about.

944
00:53:42,969 --> 00:53:45,805
Once I kill someone like that,
the ecstasy stays with me

945
00:53:45,889 --> 00:53:47,223
for a week or two.

946
00:53:47,307 --> 00:53:49,184
But after a while,

947
00:53:49,267 --> 00:53:51,811
the impulse comes back
and it's even worse.

948
00:53:51,895 --> 00:53:54,064
Then as my impulse gets stronger,

949
00:53:54,147 --> 00:53:57,734
there is no other way
than to go out and kill someone.

950
00:53:57,817 --> 00:53:59,945
I promise. Just once more.

951
00:54:00,028 --> 00:54:02,238
I want to go out and kill someone.

952
00:54:02,322 --> 00:54:03,782
I need to feel that ecstasy.

953
00:54:04,991 --> 00:54:06,034
Detective.

954
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:09,287
-Detective?
-Yes?

955
00:54:10,622 --> 00:54:11,748
Are you listening?

956
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,297
-Nam Ki-Tae.
-Yes?

957
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:23,176
Do you think it's unfair
that you were caught?

958
00:54:23,259 --> 00:54:24,427
It is unfair.

959
00:54:26,805 --> 00:54:28,014
If I hadn't gotten caught,

960
00:54:29,599 --> 00:54:31,768
I would've lived my life
traveling around the country,

961
00:54:31,851 --> 00:54:34,562
becoming the best serial killer
in history.

962
00:54:36,356 --> 00:54:38,525
It's a shame when I think about that.

963
00:54:40,402 --> 00:54:42,028
I can never do this again.

964
00:54:44,990 --> 00:54:46,032
You're right.

965
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:52,288
You won't be able to do this anymore.

966
00:55:11,933 --> 00:55:13,101
I think it's a relief.

967
00:55:13,893 --> 00:55:15,228
I was really worried.

968
00:55:15,311 --> 00:55:16,271
-He's here.
-Ha-young.

969
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:17,522
-He's here.
-He's back.

970
00:55:19,649 --> 00:55:20,859
He made a confession

971
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:23,028
about the Bongu-dong case.

972
00:55:23,111 --> 00:55:24,904
-Nam Ki-Tae is unbelievable.
-My gosh.

973
00:55:24,988 --> 00:55:27,323
Word got around about you for a reason.

974
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:29,617
I didn't know
he'd continue to confess until now.

975
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:32,162
Good work.

976
00:55:33,413 --> 00:55:34,414
Thank you.

977
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:36,291
Yes, let's go.

978
00:55:36,374 --> 00:55:38,752
-Good work.
-Good work, everyone.

979
00:55:38,835 --> 00:55:40,879
-Good work.
-Good job.

980
00:55:40,962 --> 00:55:43,381
-Good work.
-Great work.

981
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:44,466
Wait, Inspector Song.

982
00:55:46,426 --> 00:55:47,844
I heard this was yours.

983
00:55:47,927 --> 00:55:49,304
I was told to keep it well.

984
00:55:49,387 --> 00:55:50,388
I almost forgot.

985
00:55:51,848 --> 00:55:52,682
Thank you.

986
00:55:59,189 --> 00:56:01,900
-Why are you throwing this out?
-Nam Ki-Tae used that.

987
00:56:28,176 --> 00:56:29,385
Over here!

988
00:56:29,469 --> 00:56:30,887
-Nam Ki-Tae!
-Look over here!

989
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:33,264
-Move aside. Move.
-Look over here!

990
00:56:36,267 --> 00:56:39,229
<i>In 2004, the kidnapping and murder
of an elementary school student</i>

991
00:56:39,312 --> 00:56:42,440
<i>in Bongu-dong, Gyeonggi Province
almost remained unsolved,</i>

992
00:56:42,524 --> 00:56:44,943
<i>but it was also found
to be the crime of Nam Ki-Tae.</i>

993
00:56:45,026 --> 00:56:47,654
<i>This afternoon,
Nam Ki-Tae was sent to the prosecution.</i>

994
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:49,864
<i>He confessed to all the crimes</i>

995
00:56:49,948 --> 00:56:51,574
<i>he committed in the past two years.</i>

996
00:56:51,658 --> 00:56:53,827
<i>The crimes include three murders
and five attempted murders</i>

997
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:55,662
<i>in the southwestern area of Seoul,</i>

998
00:56:55,745 --> 00:56:57,247
<i>Mogu-dong Arson Murder Case,</i>

999
00:56:57,330 --> 00:56:58,748
<i>Imyeong-dong Murder Case,</i>

1000
00:56:58,832 --> 00:57:00,041
<i>two murders in Gunpo, Gyeonggi,</i>

1001
00:57:00,125 --> 00:57:01,459
<i>and in Bongu-dong,</i>

1002
00:57:01,543 --> 00:57:03,878
-<i>the kidnapping and murder.</i>
-Yoon-ji.

1003
00:57:03,962 --> 00:57:07,090
You really refuse to go out
and cover this case?

1004
00:57:07,173 --> 00:57:10,176
<i>The prosecution plans to conduct
additional investigations…</i>

1005
00:57:10,260 --> 00:57:11,636
Then what? Should I go?

1006
00:57:12,595 --> 00:57:13,930
Fine, I'll go.

1007
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:17,058
<i>Then they will decide
whether to indict him additionally.</i>

1008
00:57:18,393 --> 00:57:20,687
-Nam Ki-Tae!
-Nam Ki-Tae!

1009
00:57:28,736 --> 00:57:33,116
YEONGDEUNGPO POLICE STATION

1010
00:57:35,326 --> 00:57:37,912
Choi Yoon-ji isn't so bad,
but she never gets it right.

1011
00:57:38,538 --> 00:57:42,333
Song Ha-young throws him bait,
then Nam Ki-Tae gives him the whole story.

1012
00:57:43,084 --> 00:57:46,421
Why the heck is she going on
about people who are left behind?

1013
00:57:48,965 --> 00:57:50,341
I'm telling you.

1014
00:57:50,425 --> 00:57:53,344
He looked straight at the victims
when he killed them.

1015
00:57:54,888 --> 00:57:57,182
What do you think was on his mind?

1016
00:57:57,765 --> 00:58:00,643
It'd be awesome
if I could get an interview on that.

1017
00:58:01,644 --> 00:58:02,645
Bye.

1018
00:58:13,323 --> 00:58:15,283
Goodness, Inspector Song. Hello…

1019
00:58:15,366 --> 00:58:17,869
What? What are you doing?

1020
00:58:21,331 --> 00:58:23,291
You aren't so different from Nam Ki-Tae.

1021
00:58:23,374 --> 00:58:24,459
What did you say?

1022
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:26,711
Are you insane, you jerk?

1023
00:58:28,338 --> 00:58:30,590
Darn it, let go. Let go of me.

1024
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:32,842
How dare you disrespect
a reporter like this?

1025
00:58:33,426 --> 00:58:34,928
You're going to regret this.

1026
00:58:35,011 --> 00:58:37,013
I'll sue you immediately!

1027
00:58:38,973 --> 00:58:39,891
Listen up.

1028
00:58:39,974 --> 00:58:42,352
You completely disregard the victims
saying you have the right to know

1029
00:58:42,435 --> 00:58:44,020
as if you reporters are something.

1030
00:58:46,689 --> 00:58:49,108
You should be thankful
that I'm not suing you first.

1031
00:58:53,404 --> 00:58:55,406
That's for using my photo
without permission.

1032
00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,371
That crazy jerk.

1033
00:59:04,791 --> 00:59:06,584
-Who made this?
-Gosh, that's nice.

1034
00:59:06,668 --> 00:59:08,086
-Daddy.
-Look at Daddy.

1035
00:59:08,628 --> 00:59:10,046
-How do you feel?
-That's it.

1036
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:11,923
The weather is wonderful.

1037
00:59:12,006 --> 00:59:13,675
Thanks for making gimbap, honey.

1038
00:59:13,758 --> 00:59:16,261
What should we eat for dinner?

1039
00:59:16,344 --> 00:59:17,637
How about pizza?

1040
00:59:18,972 --> 00:59:21,391
Hey! Wait for me!

1041
00:59:29,899 --> 00:59:30,984
<i>Detective.</i>

1042
00:59:32,151 --> 00:59:34,237
<i>-Detective?
-Yes?</i>

1043
00:59:35,071 --> 00:59:36,489
<i>Song Ha-young.</i>

1044
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:38,324
<i>Detective.</i>

1045
00:59:43,871 --> 00:59:45,623
<i>Blame the girl's bad luck.</i>

1046
00:59:45,707 --> 00:59:48,626
I'm saying it's her fault
for catching my attention.

1047
00:59:48,710 --> 00:59:49,669
<i>Look at me.</i>

1048
00:59:50,628 --> 00:59:53,298
I ended up in here
trying to get some freebies.

1049
00:59:53,381 --> 00:59:56,009
<i>Well, I wouldn't say I have the right.</i>

1050
00:59:56,718 --> 00:59:58,428
But killing is sort of like my job.

1051
00:59:58,511 --> 00:59:59,762
<i>Because I need to live a long life.</i>

1052
01:00:00,346 --> 01:00:02,307
That way, I can kill more people.

1053
01:00:22,076 --> 01:00:24,370
Every time I saw her
just putting up with it,

1054
01:00:24,454 --> 01:00:25,830
it made me so angry.

1055
01:00:35,548 --> 01:00:36,966
<i>Arms and legs…</i>

1056
01:00:37,050 --> 01:00:40,386
Cut them off and divide them into two.
How many do you have?

1057
01:00:45,058 --> 01:00:47,268
<i>You know the bathroom threshold?</i>

1058
01:00:47,352 --> 01:00:48,645
The threshold…

1059
01:00:49,729 --> 01:00:52,357
is the line that separates
the living realm and underworld.

1060
01:00:55,902 --> 01:00:57,862
The line between life and death

1061
01:00:57,945 --> 01:00:59,489
which is decided and ruled by me.

1062
01:01:55,753 --> 01:01:57,463
EMERGENCY WARD

1063
01:02:05,054 --> 01:02:08,266
Ha-young! Please help!

1064
01:02:08,349 --> 01:02:10,017
My son fell into the water!

1065
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:13,229
<i>Oh, no! What do I do?</i>

1066
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:25,908
<i>Do you know how scary it is</i>

1067
01:02:25,992 --> 01:02:27,994
<i>when you're deep underwater?</i>

1068
01:02:31,998 --> 01:02:35,710
<i>She must've been scared and sad.</i>

1069
01:03:26,385 --> 01:03:28,846
TOJUNG-DONG, ANYANG, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

1070
01:03:29,388 --> 01:03:30,848
Gosh. It's freezing.

1071
01:03:44,278 --> 01:03:47,448
I'm trying to go to Daejong Lake.
Which way do I need to go?

1072
01:03:47,532 --> 01:03:48,616
Pardon?

1073
01:03:49,700 --> 01:03:51,702
You don't have to be suspicious.

1074
01:03:51,786 --> 01:03:54,163
I've never been here before.

1075
01:03:57,375 --> 01:03:58,793
There.

1076
01:03:58,876 --> 01:04:02,380
Turn right at the intersection up ahead.
And then go straight.

1077
01:04:02,463 --> 01:04:04,799
When you see another intersection,
you turn left and--

1078
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:06,008
Where are you going?

1079
01:04:06,634 --> 01:04:07,468
Pardon?

1080
01:04:07,552 --> 01:04:09,929
If you don't mind, I can give you a ride.

1081
01:04:10,763 --> 01:04:12,807
No, it's okay. I can take the bus.

1082
01:04:14,016 --> 01:04:15,935
You don't have to be suspicious.

1083
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:18,145
I'm driving down anyway.

1084
01:04:18,229 --> 01:04:20,356
If you're going in the same direction,
I'll give you a ride.

1085
01:04:20,439 --> 01:04:23,234
And you can tell me
the way to Daejong Lake.

1086
01:04:23,317 --> 01:04:24,944
That will be helpful for me.

1087
01:04:29,824 --> 01:04:32,827
Don't you have to wait
for a long time for the bus?

1088
01:04:35,246 --> 01:04:37,248
You must feel uncomfortable.

1089
01:04:38,249 --> 01:04:41,544
Then could you tell me
how to get there one more time?

1090
01:04:41,627 --> 01:04:44,171
Turn right at that intersection, and then…

1091
01:04:45,506 --> 01:04:46,591
What was that?

1092
01:04:47,174 --> 01:04:49,010
You'll see a smaller intersection.

1093
01:04:49,093 --> 01:04:52,054
-Then turn left there.
-Hold on. Let me write it down.

1094
01:04:59,854 --> 01:05:01,439
Gosh. I don't even have paper.

1095
01:05:05,318 --> 01:05:07,320
Why don't you get in
and make things easier for both of us?

1096
01:05:08,195 --> 01:05:09,405
Aren't you cold?

1097
01:05:18,122 --> 01:05:20,333
I won't refuse then.

1098
01:05:21,417 --> 01:05:22,752
No problem.

1099
01:05:23,461 --> 01:05:24,879
Please get in.

1100
01:05:24,962 --> 01:05:27,256
-You must be freezing.
-Thank you.

1101
01:05:43,064 --> 01:05:44,815
You must like dogs.

1102
01:05:56,285 --> 01:05:58,829
You can drop me off somewhere over here.

1103
01:05:59,413 --> 01:06:01,666
You just need to turn left over there.

1104
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:03,709
Right here.

1105
01:06:03,793 --> 01:06:05,419
That will do.

1106
01:06:10,216 --> 01:06:11,550
You missed it.

1107
01:06:12,176 --> 01:06:14,720
I had to go right from there.

1108
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:16,263
Drop me off here, please.

1109
01:06:16,347 --> 01:06:17,682
I'll get out here.

1110
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:20,893
Hey. Stop the car.

1111
01:06:25,606 --> 01:06:26,607
What are you doing?

1112
01:06:26,691 --> 01:06:28,776
What are you doing? Stop the car now!

1113
01:06:30,695 --> 01:06:32,446
I want a quiet ride.

1114
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:35,157
Stop the car now!
If you don't, I'll call the police!

1115
01:06:36,742 --> 01:06:38,077
I'm calling the cops.

1116
01:06:44,208 --> 01:06:45,835
Open the door!

1117
01:06:49,005 --> 01:06:50,006
Damn it.

